WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.974
<v Jamie>Jamie here, and Spirit Airlines just shut down, ending its run as the most famous US discount airline - what's the fallout, Alex?

00:00:07.974 --> 00:00:18.376
<v Alex>Alex on equities - Spirit Airlines' collapse will likely give some carriers more pricing power as they race to capture Spirit's customers, which is already being reflected in the market.

00:00:18.376 --> 00:00:21.843
<v Jamie>Right, exactly - so who's going to benefit from this?

00:00:21.843 --> 00:00:27.737
<v Alex>Well, the big airlines, of course - they'll have less competition and can charge higher prices.

00:00:27.737 --> 00:00:36.405
<v Cam>Cam on macro - and the dollar index is up zero point two seven percent overnight, which is a relatively calm reaction to the news.

00:00:36.405 --> 00:00:47.153
<v Maya>Maya from tech - and speaking of calm reactions, Palantir just posted its fastest revenue growth ever, with eighty-five percent revenue growth - that's a huge win for the company.

00:00:47.153 --> 00:00:52.354
<v Kai>Yeah, and I'm sure their "AI slop" comment had nothing to do with it.

00:00:52.354 --> 00:00:56.168
<v Maya>Oh, definitely not - they're just calling out the competition.

00:00:56.168 --> 00:01:06.916
<v Rio>Rio checking in - the human side of the Spirit Airlines story is that forty-two hundred workers are now out of a job, which is a huge blow to the community.

00:01:06.916 --> 00:01:17.665
<v Tess>Tess at retail - and it's not just the workers who are affected - the airline's collapse will also impact the travel industry as a whole, with many customers left stranded.

00:01:17.665 --> 00:01:27.373
<v Dev>Dev on crypto - meanwhile, Bitcoin is up two point two three percent today, which is a relatively small move compared to the rest of the market.

00:01:27.373 --> 00:01:32.574
<v Jamie>Yeah, it's like the crypto world is just over here, doing its own thing.

00:01:32.574 --> 00:01:37.428
<v Kai>Hey, at least they're consistent - unlike some airlines, which shall remain nameless.

00:01:37.428 --> 00:01:46.442
<v Maya>Oh, and have you seen the news about Anthropic teaming up with Goldman, Blackstone, and others on a one point five billion dollar AI venture?

00:01:46.442 --> 00:01:50.256
<v Alex>Oh, great, because what we really need is more AI.

00:01:50.256 --> 00:01:55.110
<v Maya>Hey, it's a growing market - and someone's got to capitalize on it.

00:01:55.110 --> 00:02:02.391
<v Cam>Cam on macro - and the ten-year Treasury yield is up one point five five percent, which is a significant move.

00:02:02.391 --> 00:02:04.125
<v Jamie>What's driving that, Cam?

00:02:04.125 --> 00:02:10.019
<v Cam>Well, it's likely a combination of factors, including the Fed's actions and the overall economic outlook.

00:02:10.019 --> 00:02:16.607
<v Kai>Oh, and have you seen the news about the UAE accusing Iran of renewed drone and missile attacks?

00:02:16.607 --> 00:02:25.275
<v Rio>Yes, it's a very concerning situation - and the US is trying to open the Strait of Hormuz, which is a critical waterway.

00:02:25.275 --> 00:02:30.129
<v Jamie>Okay, let's switch gears - what's the big story of the day, Alex?

00:02:30.129 --> 00:02:38.450
<v Alex>Alex on equities - well, Palantir's earnings were a huge win for the company, and their "AI slop" comment was definitely a talking point.

00:02:38.450 --> 00:02:46.772
<v Maya>Yeah, and it's not just Palantir - the whole AI industry is heating up, with companies like Anthropic and Cerebras making big moves.

00:02:46.772 --> 00:02:53.013
<v Kai>And let's not forget about the "AI slop" - I mean, who comes up with this stuff?

00:02:53.013 --> 00:02:55.440
<v Maya>Oh, it's just Palantir being Palantir.

00:02:55.440 --> 00:02:58.907
<v Jamie>Alright, alright - let's move on to quick hits.

00:02:58.907 --> 00:03:04.108
<v Tess>Tess at retail - and Pinterest just surged fifteen percent after earnings, with strong guidance.

00:03:04.108 --> 00:03:11.389
<v Dev>Dev on crypto - and Circle just jumped nearly twenty percent on the Clarity Act compromise, which preserves stablecoin rewards.

00:03:11.389 --> 00:03:15.203
<v Kai>Yeah, and I'm sure the stablecoin enthusiasts are just thrilled.

00:03:15.203 --> 00:03:22.830
<v Rio>Rio checking in - and the UK is discussing participating in a seventy-eight billion dollar European Union loan scheme to support Ukraine.

00:03:22.830 --> 00:03:31.498
<v Cam>Cam on macro - and the dollar index is still up zero point two seven percent, which is a relatively calm reaction to the news.

00:03:31.498 --> 00:03:34.619
<v Jamie>What's the odd thing of the day, Kai?

00:03:34.619 --> 00:03:43.287
<v Kai>Well, it's not every day you see a company like GameStop offering fifty-six billion dollars for eBay - I mean, what's the plan there?

00:03:43.287 --> 00:03:51.608
<v Maya>Yeah, and it's not just the price - it's the fact that GameStop is even trying to buy eBay in the first place.

00:03:51.608 --> 00:03:55.422
<v Jamie>Alright, that's a wrap - thanks for tuning in, everyone.

00:03:55.422 --> 00:04:01.316
<v Alex>And don't forget to do your own research - this show is for entertainment purposes only.

00:04:01.316 --> 00:04:06.517
<v Jamie>This show is for entertainment and education only - nothing here is investment advice.
